33.1.hd_quote: The wisdom in a weak position to recognize that survival demands complete withdrawal.
33.1.behavioral_axis: Knows to step back right after an experience to process it alone.
33.1.shadow_axis: Ghosting everyone so no lessons get transmitted.

33.2.hd_quote: The recognition that surrender to superior forces can be an opportunity to expand one's own strength and eventually triumph.
33.2.behavioral_axis: Lets the bigger force pass so it can resume reflection later, stronger.
33.2.shadow_axis: Publicly ‘private’ but not actually doing the reflection.

33.3.hd_quote: Privacy as a path to success; or A drive for privacy that will cut off its relationships, often abruptly.
33.3.behavioral_axis: Uses privacy to protect the value of the story before sharing.
33.3.shadow_axis: Cuts people off so hard the story never reaches the collective.

33.4.hd_quote: A lack of turmoil in retreat.
33.4.behavioral_axis: Shows others how to retreat gracefully and regenerate.
33.4.shadow_axis: Retreat becomes moral superiority or spiritual bypassing.

33.5.hd_quote: As important as the timing itself is the ability to keep secret one's intentions until the appropriate moment.
33.5.behavioral_axis: Holds the story until the field is ready to receive it.
33.5.shadow_axis: Leaks too early, causes confusion or gets locked away.

33.6.hd_quote: The ability to let go in retreat, to enjoy privacy.
33.6.behavioral_axis: Can stay private even when public; observes for humanity.
33.6.shadow_axis: So withdrawn the collective never benefits.
